n of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care. Each Party agrees to take all reasonable measures at its own expense to restrain its representatives from any prohibited or unauthorised disclosure or use of Confidential Information.\n\n2. Confidential Information shall at all times remain the exclusive property of the Disclosing Party. Nothing herein shall be construed as granting any licence or other rights (by implication, estoppel, or otherwise) in or to the Confidential Information, except the limited right to use such information for the Permitted Purpose.\n\n3. Within seven (7) days of a written request by the Disclosing Party, the Receiving Party shall return or destroy (as directed) all originals, copies, reproductions, and summaries of Confidential Information. The Receiving Party shall certify such return or destruction in writing.\n\n4. Neither Party shall be liable for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage. This limitation shall not apply to: (i) a Party’s breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorised disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party’s indemnity obligations under this Agreement.\n\n5. Nothing in this Agreement obligates either Party to disclose any Confidential Information. Each Party reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disclose only such information as it deems necessary in relation to the Proposed Transaction.\n\n6. This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force for a period of two (2) years from the Effective Date, unless terminated earlier by either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) year