ault governing jurisdiction:\n   India\n\n10. Never invent clauses that are not present\n    in the PROVIDED CLAUSES section	Generate a professional\nNDA\nusing the following details.\n\n==================================================\nPARTIES\n==================================================\n\nOUR COMPANY (Disclosing Party):\n\nCompany Name:\nLexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd\n\nAddress:\nMumbai, Maharashtra, India\n\nCompany Email:\nlegal@lexdraft.ai\n\nCompany Phone:\n+91-9876543210\n\n\nCLIENT (Receiving Party):\n\nClient Name:\nSwadil creation \n\nClient Company:\nNot Provided\n\nClient Address:\nNot Provided\n\n\n==================================================\nDOCUMENT REQUIREMENTS\n==================================================\n\nDocument Type:\nNDA\n\nEffective Date:\nNot Provided\n\nAgreement Term:\nNot Specified years\n\nJurisdiction:\nIndia\n\nSpecial Requirements:\nGenerate a mutual non-disclosure agreement between LexDraft Technologies and Tesla India Pvt Ltd for confidential software partnership discussions. Include confidentiality obligations, non-compete restrictions, intellectual property protection, dispute resolution under Indian law, and a 3-year confidentiality period.\n\nExtra Instructions:\nNone\n\n\n==================================================\nPROVIDED CLAUSES\n==================================================\n\nCLAUSE 1\n[Clause 1]\n\nof 4 NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT Mutual Confidentiality & Non-Disclosure This Non-Disclosure Agreement ( “Agreement” ) is made on this the [Day] day of [Month, Year] .  BY AND BETWEEN [Party 1 Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 1 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Party 1” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART ; AND [Party 2 / Company Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 2 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Company” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART .  Party 1 and Company shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as “Parties” and individually as “Party”.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 2\n[Clause 1]\n\nof 4 NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT Mutual Confidentiality & Non-Disclosure This Non-Disclosure Agreement ( “Agreement” ) is made on this the [Day] day of [Month, Year] .  BY AND BETWEEN [Party 1 Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 1 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Party 1” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART ; AND [Party 2 / Company Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 2 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Company” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART .  Party 1 and Company shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as “Parties” and individually as “Party”.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 3\n[Clause 11]\n\nby either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.  Non-Solicitation During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 4\n[Clause 11]\n\nby either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.  Non-Solicitation During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 5\n[Clause 4]\n\narty shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the “Permitted Purpose”) and for no other purpose whatsoever.  The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.  3.  Non-Disclosure Obligations The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction.  The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.  4.  Standard of Care Each Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 6\n[Clause 4]\n\narty shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the “Permitted Purpose”) and for no other purpose whatsoever.  The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.  3.  Non-Disclosure Obligations The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction.  The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.  4.  Standard of Care Each Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n\n==================================================\nGENERATION INSTRUCTIONS\n==================================================\n\n1. Generate a complete professional legal document\n\n2. Use ONLY the provided clauses as legal basis\n\n3. Fill all placeholders with real values\n\n4. Maintain professional legal formatting\n\n5. Use numbered clauses and headings\n\n6. Include:\n   - title\n   - parties section\n   - recitals\n   - obligations\n   - governing law\n   - signatures\n\n7. Do not invent unrelated legal clauses\n\n8. If uncertain about anything:\n   [REVIEW NEEDED: explanation]\n\nGenerate the complete legal document now.	MUTUAL NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Mutual Non-Disclosure Agreement ("Agreement") is made on this the [Day] day of [Month, Year].\n\nPARTIES\n\nBY AND BETWEEN LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd, a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at Mumbai, Maharashtra, India (hereinafter referred to as "Party 1", which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART;\n\nAND\n\nTesla India Pvt Ltd, a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Not Provided] (hereinafter referred to as "Party 2", which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART.\n\nParty 1 and Party 2 shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as "Parties" and individually as "Party".\n\nRECATALS\n\nWHEREAS, the Parties wish to engage in confidential discussions regarding a potential software partnership;\n\nWHEREAS, the Parties may disclose certain confidential information to each other in connection with these discussions;\n\nNOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, the Parties agree as follows:\n\n1. The Parties shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the “Permitted Purpose”) and for no other purpose whatsoever. The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.\n\n2. The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction. The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.\n\n3. Each Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n4. During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.\n\n5. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of three (3) years.\n\nGOVERNING LAW\n\nThis Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time.\n\nEXECUTION\n\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have executed this Agreement as of the date first above written.\n\n---\n\nLexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd\n\nBy: _____________________________\n\nName: _____________________________\n\nTitle: _____________________________\n\nDate: _____________________________\n\n---\n\nTesla India Pvt Ltd\n\nBy: _____________________________\n\nName: _____________________________\n\nTitle: _____________________________\n\nDate: _____________________________	llama-3.3-70b-versatile	2679	1892	archived	1	\N	2026-05-28 11:44:03.028857	2026-05-29 10:35:11.690472	\N	\N	\N	\N
