isclosing Party.\n\n2. The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction. The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.\n\n3. Each Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n4. During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.\n\n5. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of three (3) years.\n\nGOVERNING LAW\n\nThis Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time.\n\nEXECUTION\n\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have executed this Agreement as of the date first above written.\n\n---\n\nFor LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd\n\nSignature: ___________________