aharashtra, India\nEmail: legal@lexdraft.ai\nPhone: +91-9876543210\n\nand\n\n**Swadil creation** ("Receiving Party")\nwith its principal place of business at Not Provided\n\n**RECITALS**\n\nWHEREAS, the Disclosing Party and the Receiving Party are interested in evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing a proposed transaction (the "Proposed Transaction"); and\n\nWHEREAS, in connection with the Proposed Transaction, the Disclosing Party may disclose certain confidential and proprietary information to the Receiving Party;\n\nNOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, the parties agree as follows:\n\n1. **USE OF CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION**\nThe Receiving Party shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the “Permitted Purpose”) and for no other purpose whatsoever. The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.\n\n2. **NON-DISCLOSURE OBLIGATIONS**\nThe Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction. The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.\n\n3. **STANDARD OF CARE**\nEach Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n4. **OWNERSHIP AND NO LICENCE**\nConfidential Information shall at all times remain the exclusive property of the Disclosing Party. Nothing herein shall be construed as granting any licence or other rights (by implication, estoppel, or otherwise) in or to the Confidential Information, except the limited right to use such information for the Permitted Purpose.\n\n5. **RETURN OR DESTRUCTION**\nWithin seven (7) days of a written request by the Disclosing Party, the Receiving Party shall return or destroy (as directed) all originals, copies, reproductions, and summaries of Confidential Information. The Receiving Party shall certify such return or destruction in writing.\n\n6. **LIMITATION OF LIABILITY**\nNeither Party shall be liable for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage. This limitation shall not apply to: (i) a Party’s breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorised disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party’s indemnity obligations under this Agreement.\n\n7. **TERM AND TERMINATION**\nThis Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force until the Proposed Transaction is discontinued by either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.\n\n8. **GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION**\nThis Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Indian Arbitration Act.\n\n**IN WITNESS WHEREOF**\n\nThe parties have executed this Agreement as of the date first above written.\n\n**LEXDRAFT LEGAL SOLUTIONS PVT LTD**\n\nBy: _____________________________\nName: _____________________________\nTitle: _____________________________\nDate: _____________________________\n\n**SWADIL CREATION**\n\