itals/background\n   - definitions section\n   - obligations/responsibilities\n   - confidentiality clauses\n   - indemnification clauses\n   - limitation of liability\n   - governing law\n   - dispute resolution\n   - termination clauses\n   - signature blocks\n\n6B. Maintain enterprise legal formatting with:\n   - numbered clauses\n   - proper spacing\n   - formal legal tone\n   - section headings\n   - professional readability\n   \n8. If uncertain about anything:\n   [REVIEW NEEDED: explanation]\n\nGenerate the complete legal document now.\nIMPORTANT FINAL VALIDATION:\n\n- Ensure all party names are correct\n- Ensure no unrelated entities appear\n- Ensure no placeholder text remains\n- Ensure all clauses are legally coherent\n- Ensure formatting is professional and review-ready	CONFIDENTIALITY AND NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure Agreement ("Agreement") is made and entered into on this 30th day of May, 2026 ("Effective Date") by and between:\n\n**LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd**, a company incorporated under the laws of India, with its registered office at Mumbai, Maharashtra, India, and email address at legal@lexdraft.ai, phone number +91-9876543210 ("Disclosing Party");\n\n**Swadil Technologies Pvt Ltd**, a company incorporated under the laws of India, with its registered office at Mumbai, Maharashtra, India, represented by its authorized representative **Swadil creation** ("Receiving Party");\n\n**RECITALS**\n\nWHEREAS, the Disclosing Party and the Receiving Party are interested in exploring a potential business opportunity (the "Proposed Transaction");\n\nWHEREAS, in connection with the Proposed Transaction, the Disclosing Party may disclose certain confidential and proprietary information to the Receiving Party;\n\nWHEREAS, the Receiving Party is willing to receive such confidential and proprietary information on the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement.\n\n**DEFINITIONS**\n\nFor the purposes of this Agreement, the following definitions shall apply:\n\n* "Confidential Information" means all information, whether written or oral, that is disclosed by the Disclosing Party to the Receiving Party in connection with the Proposed Transaction, including but not limited to trade secrets, business plans, financial information, and technical data.\n\n**OBLIGATIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES**\n\n1. The Receiving Party shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the "Permitted Purpose") and for no other purpose whatsoever. The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.\n2. The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarize, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction. The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.\n3. Each Party shall protect the other's Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n**CONFIDENTIALITY CLAUSES**\n\n4. The Receiving Party shall not disclose any Confidential Information to any third party without the prior written consent of the Disclosing Party.\n5. The Receiving Party shall not use any Confidential Information for any purpose other than the Permitted Purpose.\n\n**INDEMNIFICATION CLAUSES**\n\n6. The Receiving Party shall indemnify and hold harmless the Disclosing Party against any and all claims, damages, losses, and expenses arising out of or related to any breach of this Agreement by the Receiving Party.\n\n**LIMITATION OF LIABILITY**\n\n7. In no event shall either Party be liable for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage. This limitation shall not apply to: (i) a Party's breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorized disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party's indemnity obligations under this Agreement.\n\n**TERM AND TERMINATION**\n\n8. This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force for a period of three (3) years from the Effective Date.\n9. Upon expiration or termination of this Agreement, the Receiving Party shall return all Confidential Information to the Disclosing Party and shall destroy any copies thereof.\n\n**NON-SOLICITATION**\n\n10. During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.\n\n**GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION**\n\n11. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India.\n12. Any disputes arising out of or related to this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time.\n\n**EXECUTION**\n\nBy signing below, the Parties acknowledge that they have read, understand, and agree to be bound by the terms and conditions of this Agreement.\n\n---\n\n**Disclosing Party**\n\nLexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd\n\nBy: _______________________________\n\nName: _______________________________\n\nTitle: _______________________________\n\nDate: _______________________________\n\n**Receiving Party**\n\nSwadil Technologies Pvt Ltd\n\nBy: _______________________________\n\nName: _______________________________\n\nTitle: _______________________________\n\nDate: _______________________________\n\nNote: This document is generated based on the provided clauses and may require review and modification to ensure compliance with applicable laws and regulations. [REVIEW NEEDED: Ensure all clauses are legally coherent and compliant with applicable laws and regulations.]	llama-3.3-70b-versatile	3331	2751	archived	3	\N	2026-05-29 08:37:08.755338	2026-05-29 10:15:15.201977	\N	\N	\N	\N
