ny client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 5\n[Clause 1]\n\nof 4 NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT Mutual Confidentiality & Non-Disclosure This Non-Disclosure Agreement ( “Agreement” ) is made on this the [Day] day of [Month, Year] .  BY AND BETWEEN [Party 1 Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 1 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Party 1” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART ; AND [Party 2 / Company Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 2 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Company” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART .  Party 1 and Company shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as “Parties” and individually as “Party”.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 6\n[Clause 1]\n\nof 4 NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT Mutual Confidentiality & Non-Disclosure This Non-Disclosure Agreement ( “Agreement” ) is made on this the [Day] day of [Month, Year] .  BY AND BETWEEN [Party 1 Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 1 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Party 1” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART ; AND [Party 2 / Company Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 2 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Company” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context