n\nThis Non-Disclosure Agreement ("Agreement") is made on this the 29th day of May, 2002.\n\nBY AND BETWEEN LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd, a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at Mumbai, Maharashtra, India (hereinafter referred to as "Party 1", which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART;\n\nAND Darshan Mali, representing TheWebloom.tech, having its registered office at pathardi phata, nashik 422010 (hereinafter referred to as "Party 2", which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART.\n\nParty 1 and Party 2 shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as "Parties" and individually as "Party".\n\nWHEREAS, the Parties wish to engage in discussions regarding a potential business opportunity (the "Proposed Transaction"); and\n\nWHEREAS, in connection with such discussions, each Party may disclose certain confidential and proprietary information to the other Party.\n\nNOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, the Parties agree as follows:\n\n1. NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT \nMutual Confidentiality & Non-Disclosure\n\nThis Non-Disclosure Agreement ( “Agreement” ) is made on this the 29th day of May, 2002. \nBY AND BETWEEN LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd, a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at Mumbai, Maharashtra, India (hereinafter referred to as “Party 1” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART ; \nAND Darshan Mali, representing TheWebloom.tech, having its registered office at pathardi phata, nashik 422010 (hereinafter referred to as “Party 2” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART . \nParty 1 and Party 2 shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as “Parties” and individually as “Party”.\n\n2. CONFIDENTIALITY OBLIGATIONS\nNothing in this Agreement obligates either Party to disclose any Confidential Information. Each Party reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disclose only such information as it deems necessary in relation to the Proposed Transaction.\n\n3. TERM & TERMINATION\nThis Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force for a period of 2 years from the date of execution. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.\n\n4. NON-SOLICITATION\nDuring the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party. This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.\n\n5. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\nNeither Party shall be liable for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage. This limitation shall not apply to: (i) a Party’s breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorized disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party’s indemnity obligations under this Agreement.\n\n6. INDEMNIFICATION\n[REVIEW NEEDED: This clause is not provided in the given clauses, but it is mentioned in Clause 5. It is recommended to add a proper indemnification clause to the agreement.]\n\n7. GOVERNING LAW\nThis Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time.\n\n8. DISPUTE RESOLUTION\nAny disputes arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time.\n\nBy signing below, the Parties acknowledge that they have read, understand, and agree to be bound by the terms and conditions of this Agreement.\n\n---\n\n**Party 1 (LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd)**\n\nSignature: _____________________________\nName: _____________________________\nTitle: _____________________________\nDate: _____________________________\n\n**Party 2 (Darshan Mali, representing TheWebloom.tech)**\n\nSignature: _____________________________\nName: _____________________________\nTitle: _____________________________\nDate: _____________________________	llama-3.3-70b-versatile	3336	3488	draft	2	\N	2026-05-29 10:16:04.404628	2026-05-29 10:16:04.404628	\N	\N	\N	\N
