and other proprietary information.\n* "Proposed Transaction" means the potential business opportunity being explored by the parties.\n\n## OBLIGATIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n1. The Receiving Party shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the "Permitted Purpose") and for no other purpose whatsoever.\n2. The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.\n3. The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarize, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction.\n4. The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.\n5. Each Party shall protect the other's Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n## CONFIDENTIALITY\n\nThe Receiving Party shall maintain the confidentiality of the Confidential Information and shall not disclose it to any third party without the prior written consent of the Disclosing Party.\n\n## INDEMNIFICATION\n\nThe Receiving Party shall indemnify and hold harmless the Disclosing Party against any and all claims, damages, and expenses arising out of or related to any breach of this Agreement by the Receiving Party.\n\n## LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\n\nNeither Party shall be liable to the other for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage. This limitation shall not apply to: (i) a Party's breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorized disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party's indemnity obligations under this Agreement.\n\n## TERM AND TERMINATION\n\nThis Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force for a period of 3 years from the Effective Date. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of 5 years.\n\n## NON-SOLICITATION\n\nDuring the term of this Agreement and for 12 months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.\n\n## GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION\n\nThis Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising out of or related to this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time.\n\n## ENTIRE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties with respect to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior or contemporaneous agreements or understandings.\n\nBy signing below, the parties acknowledge that they have read, understand, and agree to be bound by the terms and conditions of this Agreement.\n\n---\n\n**LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd**\n\nSignature