ty, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 5\n[Clause 4]\n\narty shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the “Permitted Purpose”) and for no other purpose whatsoever.  The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.  3.  Non-Disclosure Obligations The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction.  The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.  4.  Standard of Care Each Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 6\n[Clause 4]\n\narty shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implemen