mnification, limitation of liability, arbitration clause, and termination provisions.\nGenerate a highly professional enterprise-grade NDA agreement suitable for technology partnership discussions. Use formal legal language, structured numbered clauses, proper section headings, definitions, confidentiality protections, governing law, dispute resolution, and signature sections.\n\nExtra Instructions:\nNone\n\n\n==================================================\nPROVIDED CLAUSES\n==================================================\n\nCLAUSE 1\n[Clause 10]\n\ne for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage.  This limitation shall not a pply to: (i) a Party’s breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorised disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party’s indemnity obligations under Clause 12.  14.  No Obligation to Disclose of 4 Nothing in this Agreement obligates either Party to disclose any Confidential Information.  Each Party reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disclose only such information as it deems necessary in relation to the Proposed Transaction.  15.  Term & Termination This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force until the Proposed Transaction is discontinued by either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 2\n[Clause 10]\n\ne for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage.  This limitation shall not a pply to: (i) a Party’s breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorised disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party’s indemnity obligations under Clause 12.  14.  No Obligation to Disclose of 4 Nothing in this Agreement obligates either Party to disclose any Confidential Information.  Each Party reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disclose only such information as it deems necessary in relation to the Proposed Transaction.  15.  Term & Termination This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force until the Proposed Transaction is discontinued by either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 3\n[Clause 4]\n\narty shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the “Permitted Purpose”) and for no other purpose whatsoever.  The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.  3.  Non-Disclosure Obligations The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction.  The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.  4.  Standard of Care Each Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 4\n[Clause 4]\n\narty shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the “Permitted Purpose”) and for no other purpose whatsoever.  The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.  3.  Non-Disclosure Obligations The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarise, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction.  The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.  4.  Standard of Care Each Party shall protect the other’s Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 5\n[Clause 11]\n\nby either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.  Non-Solicitation During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 6\n[Clause 11]\n\nby either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.  Non-Solicitation During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n==================================================\nGENERATION INSTRUCTIONS\n==================================================\n\n1. Generate a complete professional legal document\n\n2. Use ONLY the provided clauses as legal basis\n\n3. Fill all placeholders with the EXACT values provided in the live form data.\n\n4. ALWAYS prioritize:\n   - client_name\n   - client_company\n   - jurisdiction\n   - effective_date\n   - agreement term\n   from the live form input over any names, examples,\n   or sample entities found in retrieved clauses.\n\n5. NEVER reuse company names, people names,\n   addresses, or examples found inside retrieved clauses.\n\n6. Retrieved clauses are ONLY for:\n   - legal structure\n   - clause language\n   - compliance logic\n   - formatting guidance\n\n7. ALL final entity names in the generated document\n   must come ONLY from the submitted form data.\n\n6A. The generated document MUST contain:\n\n   - professional legal title\n   - parties section\n   - recitals/background\n   - definitions section\n   - obligations/responsibilities\n   - confidentiality clauses\n   - indemnification clauses\n   - limitation of liability\n   - governing law\n   - dispute resolution\n   - termination clauses\n   - signature blocks\n\n6B. Maintain enterprise legal formatting with:\n   - numbered clauses\n   - proper spacing\n   - formal legal tone\n   - section headings\n   - professional readability\n   \n8. If uncertain about anything:\n   [REVIEW NEEDED: explanation]\n\nGenerate the complete legal document now.\nIMPORTANT FINAL VALIDATION:\n\n- Ensure all party names are correct\n- Ensure no unrelated entities appear\n- Ensure no placeholder text remains\n- Ensure all clauses are legally coherent\n- Ensure formatting is professional and review-ready	CONFIDENTIALITY AND NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure Agreement ("Agreement") is made and entered into on this 29th day of May, 2026 ("Effective Date") by and between:\n\n**LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd** ("Disclosing Party")\nwith its principal place of business at Mumbai, Maharashtra, India\nand\n**Swadil Technologies Pvt Ltd** ("Receiving Party")\nwith its principal place of business at Nashik, Maharashtra, India-422009\n\n**RECITALS**\n\nWHEREAS, the Disclosing Party and the Receiving Party are considering a potential business partnership and wish to exchange confidential information in connection with such discussions; and\nWHEREAS, the parties wish to ensure that any confidential information exchanged is protected and used solely for the purpose of evaluating and negotiating the potential partnership.\n\n**DEFINITIONS**\n\nFor the purposes of this Agreement, the following definitions shall apply:\n\n* "Confidential Information" means all information, whether written or oral, that is disclosed by the Disclosing Party to the Receiving Party, including but not limited to trade secrets, business plans, financial information, and technical data.\n* "Proposed Transaction" means the potential business partnership between the Disclosing Party and the Receiving Party.\n\n**OBLIGATIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES**\n\n1. The Receiving Party shall use the Confidential Information solely for evaluating, negotiating, and, if applicable, implementing the Proposed Transaction (the "Permitted Purpose") and for no other purpose whatsoever.\n2. The Receiving Party shall not use the Confidential Information, directly or indirectly, for its own benefit or for the benefit of any third party, except as expressly permitted in writing by the Disclosing Party.\n3. The Receiving Party shall not disclose, reproduce, summarize, or distribute Confidential Information except in connection with the Proposed Transaction.\n4. The Receiving Party may share Confidential Information only with its employees and consultants on a strict need-to-know basis, provided that such persons are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.\n5. Each Party shall protect the other's Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own proprietary information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care.\n\n**CONFIDENTIALITY CLAUSES**\n\n6. The Receiving Party shall not disclose any Confidential Information to any third party without the prior written consent of the Disclosing Party.\n7. The Receiving Party shall ensure that its employees and consultants who have access to Confidential Information are aware of the confidential nature of such information and are bound by written Confidentiality obligations no less restrictive than those set out herein.\n\n**INDEMNIFICATION CLAUSES**\n\n8. The Receiving Party shall indemnify and hold harmless the Disclosing Party against any and all claims, damages, and expenses arising out of or related to any breach of this Agreement by the Receiving Party.\n\n**LIMITATION OF LIABILITY**\n\n9. In no event shall either Party be liable for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage.\n10. This limitation shall not apply to: (i) a Party's breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorized disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party's indemnity obligations under this Agreement.\n\n**GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION**\n\n11. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India.\n12. Any disputes arising out of or related to this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time.\n\n**TERMINATION**\n\n13. This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force for a period of 3 years from the Effective Date.\n14. Either Party may terminate this Agreement upon thirty (30) days' prior written notice to the other Party.\n15. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.\n\n**NON-SOLICITATION**\n\n16. During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.\n\n**EXECUTION**\n\nBy signing below, the parties acknowledge that they have read, understand, and agree to be bound by the terms and conditions of this Agreement.\n\n---\n\n**LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd**\n\nSignature: _____________________________\nName: _____________________________\nTitle: _____________________________\nDate: _____________________________\n\n**Swadil Technologies Pvt Ltd**\n\nSignature: _____________________________\nName: _____________________________\nTitle: _____________________________\nDate: _____________________________	llama-3.3-70b-versatile	3309	4033	archived	1	\N	2026-05-29 08:17:28.214559	2026-05-29 10:15:36.745181	\N	\N	\N	\N
