 NEEDED: describe issue]\n\n6. Output clean plain text\n\n7. The document must be complete and ready\n   for professional legal review\n\n8. Apply this letterhead style:\n   Use formal Indian corporate legal document formatting with professional headings and signature sections\n\n9. Default governing jurisdiction:\n   India\n\n10. Never invent clauses that are not present\n    in the PROVIDED CLAUSES section	Generate a professional\nNDA\nusing the following details.\n\n==================================================\nPARTIES\n==================================================\n\nOUR COMPANY (Disclosing Party):\n\nCompany Name:\nLexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd\n\nAddress:\nMumbai, Maharashtra, India\n\nCompany Email:\nlegal@lexdraft.ai\n\nCompany Phone:\n+91-9876543210\n\n\nCLIENT (Receiving Party):\n\nClient Name:\nDarshan Mali\n\nClient Company:\nTheWebloom.tech\n\nClient Address:\npathardi phata,nashik 422010\n\n\n==================================================\nDOCUMENT REQUIREMENTS\n==================================================\n\nDocument Type:\nNDA\n\nEffective Date:\n2002-05-29\n\nAgreement Term:\n2 years\n\nJurisdiction:\nIndia\n\nSpecial Requirements:\nInclude confidentiality obligations, indemnification, limitation of liability, arbitration clause, and intellectual property protections.Generate a highly professional enterprise-grade NDA agreement with proper legal formatting, clause numbering, signature sections, dispute resolution, governing law, and confidentiality protections.\n\n\nExtra Instructions:\nNone\n\n\n==================================================\nPROVIDED CLAUSES\n==================================================\n\nCLAUSE 1\n[Clause 10]\n\ne for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage.  This limitation shall not a pply to: (i) a Party’s breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorised disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party’s indemnity obligations under Clause 12.  14.  No Obligation to Disclose of 4 Nothing in this Agreement obligates either Party to disclose any Confidential Information.  Each Party reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disclose only such information as it deems necessary in relation to the Proposed Transaction.  15.  Term & Termination This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force until the Proposed Transaction is discontinued by either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 2\n[Clause 10]\n\ne for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage.  This limitation shall not a pply to: (i) a Party’s breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorised disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party’s indemnity obligations under Clause 12.  14.  No Obligation to Disclose of 4 Nothing in this Agreement obligates either Party to disclose any Confidential Information.  Each Party reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disclose only such information as it deems necessary in relation to the Proposed Transaction.  15.  Term & Termination This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force until the Proposed Transaction is discontinued by either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 3\n[Clause 11]\n\nby either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.  Non-Solicitation During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 4\n[Clause 11]\n\nby either Party upon thirty (30) days’ prior written notice.  The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.  16.  Non-Solicitation During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not: (a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement; (b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party; or (c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.  This Clause shall not restrict either Party from responding to general job advertisements or engaging persons who independently approach them without prior solicitation in breach of this Clause.  17.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 5\n[Clause 1]\n\nof 4 NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT Mutual Confidentiality & Non-Disclosure This Non-Disclosure Agreement ( “Agreement” ) is made on this the [Day] day of [Month, Year] .  BY AND BETWEEN [Party 1 Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 1 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Party 1” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART ; AND [Party 2 / Company Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 2 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Company” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART .  Party 1 and Company shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as “Parties” and individually as “Party”.\n\n\n\nCLAUSE 6\n[Clause 1]\n\nof 4 NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT Mutual Confidentiality & Non-Disclosure This Non-Disclosure Agreement ( “Agreement” ) is made on this the [Day] day of [Month, Year] .  BY AND BETWEEN [Party 1 Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 1 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Party 1” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART ; AND [Party 2 / Company Legal Name] , a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at [Party 2 Address] (hereinafter referred to as “Company” , which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART .  Party 1 and Company shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as “Parties” and individually as “Party”.\n\n\n==================================================\nGENERATION INSTRUCTIONS\n==================================================\n\n1. Generate a complete professional legal document\n\n2. Use ONLY the provided clauses as legal basis\n\n3. Fill all placeholders with the EXACT values provided in the live form data.\n\n4. ALWAYS prioritize:\n   - client_name\n   - client_company\n   - jurisdiction\n   - effective_date\n   - agreement term\n   from the live form input over any names, examples,\n   or sample entities found in retrieved clauses.\n\n5. NEVER reuse company names, people names,\n   addresses, or examples found inside retrieved clauses.\n\n6. Retrieved clauses are ONLY for:\n   - legal structure\n   - clause language\n   - compliance logic\n   - formatting guidance\n\n7. ALL final entity names in the generated document\n   must come ONLY from the submitted form data.\n\n6A. The generated document MUST contain:\n\n   - professional legal title\n   - parties section\n   - recitals/background\n   - definitions section\n   - obligations/responsibilities\n   - confidentiality clauses\n   - indemnification clauses\n   - limitation of liability\n   - governing law\n   - dispute resolution\n   - termination clauses\n   - signature blocks\n\n6B. Maintain enterprise legal formatting with:\n   - numbered clauses\n   - proper spacing\n   - formal legal tone\n   - section headings\n   - professional readability\n   \n8. If uncertain about anything:\n   [REVIEW NEEDED: explanation]\n\nGenerate the complete legal document now.\nIMPORTANT FINAL VALIDATION:\n\n- Ensure all party names are correct\n- Ensure no unrelated entities appear\n- Ensure no placeholder text remains\n- Ensure all clauses are legally coherent\n- Ensure formatting is professional and review-ready	NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Non-Disclosure Agreement ("Agreement") is made on this the 29th day of May, 2002.\n\nBY AND BETWEEN LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd, a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, having its registered office at Mumbai, Maharashtra, India (hereinafter referred to as "Party 1", which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the ONE PART;\n\nAND Darshan Mali, representing TheWebloom.tech, having its registered office at pathardi phata, nashik 422010 (hereinafter referred to as "Party 2", which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context, include its representatives and permitted assigns) of the OTHER PART.\n\nParty 1 and Party 2 shall hereinafter be referred to collectively as "Parties" and individually as "Party".\n\n## RECITALS\n\nWHEREAS, the Parties wish to engage in discussions regarding a potential business opportunity;\n\nWHEREAS, in connection with such discussions, each Party may disclose certain confidential and proprietary information to the other Party;\n\nWHEREAS, the Parties wish to ensure that such confidential information is protected and maintained in confidence.\n\n## DEFINITIONS\n\nFor the purposes of this Agreement, the following definitions shall apply:\n\n* "Confidential Information" means all information, whether written or oral, that is disclosed by one Party to the other Party, including but not limited to trade secrets, business plans, financial information, and technical data.\n\n## OBLIGATIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n1. The Parties agree to maintain the confidentiality of all Confidential Information disclosed by the other Party.\n2. The Parties agree not to use any Confidential Information for any purpose other than in connection with the potential business opportunity.\n3. The Parties agree not to disclose any Confidential Information to any third party without the prior written consent of the other Party.\n\n## CONFIDENTIALITY\n\n4. Nothing in this Agreement obligates either Party to disclose any Confidential Information. Each Party reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to disclose only such information as it deems necessary in relation to the potential business opportunity.\n\n## TERM AND TERMINATION\n\n5. This Agreement shall become effective on the date of execution by both Parties and shall remain in force for a period of 2 years.\n6. The Confidentiality and non-use obligations shall survive the expiry or termination of this Agreement for a period of five (5) years.\n\n## NON-SOLICITATION\n\n7. During the term of this Agreement and for twelve (12) months after its expiry or termination, each Party agrees that, without the prior written consent of the other Party, it shall not:\n(a) directly or indirectly solicit for employment, engagement, or consultancy any employee, officer, key consultant, or contractor of the other Party with whom it had material dealings in connection with this Agreement;\n(b) induce or attempt to induce any such person to leave or alter their relationship with the other Party;\n(c) directly or indirectly solicit, canvass, or induce any client, customer, or key business partner of the other Party to reduce, cease, or materially alter its business relationship with that Party.\n\n## INDEMNIFICATION\n\n8. The Receiving Party shall indemnify and hold harmless the Disclosing Party against any and all claims, damages, and expenses arising out of or related to any breach of this Agreement by the Receiving Party.\n\n## LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\n\n9. In no event shall either Party be liable for any special, consequential, incidental, or exemplary damages or loss (including lost profits or business opportunity) regardless of whether a Party was advised of the possibility of such damage.\nThis limitation shall not apply to: (i) a Party's breach of its Confidentiality obligations under this Agreement; (ii) any misuse or unauthorized disclosure of Confidential Information; or (iii) the Receiving Party's indemnity obligations under this Agreement.\n\n## GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION\n\n10. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India.\n11. Any disputes arising out of or related to this Agreement shall be resolved through arbitration in accordance with the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996.\n\n## TERMINATION\n\n12. This Agreement may be terminated by either Party upon thirty (30) days' prior written notice to the other Party.\n\nBy signing below, the Parties acknowledge that they have read, understand, and agree to be bound by the terms and conditions of this Agreement.\n\n---\n\n**LexDraft Legal Solutions Pvt Ltd**\n\nSignature: _____________________________\nName: _____________________________\nTitle: _____________________________\nDate: _____________________________\n\n**Darshan Mali, representing TheWebloom.tech**\n\nSignature: _____________________________\nName: _____________________________\nTitle: _____________________________\nDate: _____________________________	llama-3.3-70b-versatile	3201	2549	archived	1	\N	2026-05-29 08:40:30.392245	2026-05-29 10:15:40.831225	exports/lexdraft_darshan_mali_2026-05-29_9264.docx	\N	2026-05-29 10:15:55.340027	\N
